sentence: Consumer products maker The Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) on Thursday posted mixed fiscal first quarter earnings results and offered a tepid second quarter outlook.
The Cincinnati-based company reported fiscal first quarter net income of $2.81 billion, or 96 cents per share, compared with $3.02 billion, or $1.03 per share, in the year-ago period.
Excluding special items, adjusted profit was $1.06 per share.
Revenue fell 3.7% from last year to $20.7 billion.
On average, Wall Street analysts expected a smaller profit of 96 cents per share, albeit on higher revenue of $20.79 billion.
Looking ahead, PG forecast second quarter earnings of $1.07 to $1.09 per share, which would miss analysts' outlook for $1.10 per share.
For the full fiscal year 2013, the company reiterated its prior outlook for earnings of $3.80 to $4, which straddles Wall Street's estimate of $3.90 per share for the year.
Shares of Procter & Gamble ( PG ) have a 3.30% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $68.08.
The stock has technical support in the $64-$65 price area.
The stock is trading near the all-time high range of $70-$73 a share.
